*** THE MISSION ***

My goal here is to make a new theme for Ph7cms. The current theme is usable but I really want it to look and feel a different. 

*** HOW ***

Most of this will be done using CSS but there will be some rearanging involved, for example the top and bottom menu template files. 
We will need to rearrange the order and in some cases the location of the nav bars links to the other pages in order to allow our 
new CSS rules to work. This in turn will require some changes in the routes scrip. 

*** MAYBE *** 

I would like to add a few more feilds to the Current ones available in the users profile, this is an option now
however these additions are limited to text or number feilds. I would like the ability to add radio and checkbox,
and button input types, however this is a little more involved will require changes in view forms, models and also
controllers so this may be an extra I might include at the end of the project.

*** CURRENT LAYOUT (USER SIDE)***

All the search pages should be linked on there mother catagory pages not seprate links that add extra confusion to navigation.

